title:weigh someone down

<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>weigh someone down • weigh someone up</xh5><p> <i>weigh someone down</i>—(also: weight someone down) 1. press on a person with a heavy weight: Get this bundle off my back; it’s really <u>weighing me down</u>. 2. make smb. very sad; depress a person: When an American girl does that, you can guess there’s something “mighty hefty” <u>weighing her down</u>.</p><p> <i>weigh someone up</i>—(coll.) form an opinion about a person: “I knew too much about her,” she said. “I had <u>weighed her up</u>.”</p> </entry>
